{"id":1772,"date":"2022-11-01T16:49:00","date_gmt":"2022-11-01T20:49:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/synergylife.coach\/?p=1772"},"modified":"2022-11-02T15:45:28","modified_gmt":"2022-11-02T19:45:28","slug":"thriving-in-ministry-clergy-clergy-wives-peer-learning-groups","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/synergylife.coach\/thriving-in-ministry-clergy-clergy-wives-peer-learning-groups\/","title":{"rendered":"Thriving in Ministry: Clergy\/Clergy Wives Peer Learning Groups"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/synergylife.coach\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/TiM-logo-white-on-black.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1776\" width=\"143\" height=\"181\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h1 class=\"has-text-align-center wp-block-heading\"><strong>Thriving in Ministry<\/strong><\/h1>\n\n\n\n<p>Founding Synergy Life Coaching prepared me for yet another ministry opportunity.  This past summer (2022) Mka. Rozanne and I were invited to join the&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https:\/\/thrivingorthodox.org\/?msclkid=5389a3dac64111ec8fff35525265b9e5?msclkid=5389a3dac64111ec8fff35525265b9e5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Thriving in Ministry<\/a><\/em>&nbsp;(TiM) team as facilitators for Clergy Peer Learning Groups (Fr. David) and Clergy Wives Peer Learning Groups (Mka. Rozanne). As noted on their website, in 2018 the OCA was awarded a generous grant through the Lilly Endowment to further develop a program of Peer Learning to support Orthodox&nbsp;clergy and clergy wives.&nbsp;<em>Thriving in Ministry<\/em> (TiM) is that resource for clergy and clergy wives, administered by the Orthodox Church in America&#8217;s (<a href=\"https:\/\/www.oca.org\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">OCA<\/a>)&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.oca.org\/about\/boards-offices-commissions\/pastoral-life\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Office of Pastoral Life<\/a>, and has groups meeting from coast to coast.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When we returned from Alaska in 2019, I had made one-on-one\u00a0mentoring and small groups a ministry priority, and\u00a0<em>Thriving in Ministry<\/em>\u00a0fits this priority perfectly! I am currently facilitating two Clergy Peer Learning Groups (CPLG): one in North Florida and one in Middle-Georgia. Mka. Rozanne is currently forming her first Clergy Wives Peer Learning Group (CWPLG). Both of us believe that facilitating trusting relationships, encouragement, and refueling among clergy\/clergy wives through these peer learning groups is one of the greatest contributions we can make to the Church as a whole at this time. Please contact either one of us if you are interested in learning more about TiM and peer learning groups or you know someone who might be.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Thriving in Ministry Founding Synergy Life Coaching prepared me for yet another ministry opportunity. This past summer (2022) Mka. Rozanne and I were invited to join the&nbsp;Thriving in Ministry&nbsp;(TiM) team as facilitators for Clergy Peer Learning Groups (Fr. David) and Clergy Wives Peer Learning Groups (Mka. Rozanne). As noted on their website, in 2018 the [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[22,23,26,24,25,27,21,20],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/synergylife.coach\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1772"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/synergylife.coach\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/synergylife.coach\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/synergylife.coach\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/synergylife.coach\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1772"}],"version-history":[{"count":8,"href":"https:\/\/synergylife.coach\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1772\/r